  DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN

    The xconsole program displays messages which are usually sent to /dev/
    console.

  OOPPTTIIOONNSS

    Xconsole accepts all of the standard X Toolkit command line options along
    with the additional options listed below:
    --ffiillee file-name
        To monitor some other device, use this option to specify the device
        name. This does not work on regular files as they are always ready to
        be read from.

    --nnoottiiffyy --nnoonnoottiiffyy
        When new data are received from the console and the notify option is
        set, the icon name of the application has " *" appended, so that it is
        evident even when the application is iconified. -notify is the
        default.

    --ddaaeemmoonn
        This option causes xconsole to place itself in the background, using
        fork/exit.

    --vveerrbboossee
        When set, this option directs xconsole to display an informative
        message in the first line of the text buffer.

    --eexxiittOOnnFFaaiill
        When set, this option directs xconsole to exit when it is unable to
        redirect the console output.

